The paper deals with the linear complexity of pseudorandom binary sequences, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The sequences are derived from Euler quotients, which involve number theory (cs.NT). The paper also establishes a recursive relation, which is a common technique in computer science (cs.DS) and the results may have practical applications in software engineering (cs.SE).
